title: T-Bone Walker Best of @ 320kbps
description:
T-Bone Walker, one of the relatively unknown blues greats. This is the guy that first wowed Hendrix as a kid by playing behind is head, a trick Jimi later copied. 
BB King said of him "In 1940 or &#039;42, I believe, I heard a certain T-Bone Walker and it was the first time I had heard an electric guitar; I went crazy, he had the smoothest touch I had ever heard in a guitarist."

Good stuff. 

SHARING IS CARING. Seed
